<div id="container_txt"><!--enpcontent--><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px"><strong>China.org.cn,</strong> China&#39;s national online news service based in Beijing, offers wide-ranging, up-to-date news about China and information about Chinese history, politics, economics and culture.</p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px"><strong>Job vacancy in Beijing</strong></p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px"><strong>Job title: English copy editor</strong></p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px"><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px">* Editing, reporting and writing news reports, feature stories, and opinion articles.</p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px">* Assisting in editorial decision-making, including project planning, story selection and page design.</p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px">* Helping to train reporters and translators.</p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px"><strong>The successful candidate must:</strong></p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px">* Be a native English speaker with strong writing skills.</p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px">* Hold a Bachelor’s degree or higher, and ideally a professional qualification in journalism.</p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px">* Be a self-starter and a team player; able to work to deadlines; have a good news sense and some knowledge of Chinese affairs.</p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px">* Be computer literate.</p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px"><strong>The preferred candidate will have:</strong></p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px">* No less than two years’ experience of writing, editing, producing print, broadcast or online content.</p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px"><strong>Benefits:</strong></p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px">Package includes competitive salary, 20 paid vacation days and medical program.</p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px">Please send an email with a full CV and examples of work if possible to recruitment@china.org.cn. Only short-listed candidates will be contacted.</p><p style="MARGIN: 0px 3px 15px"><!